 Damilola Mike-Bamiloye has premiered a new short film on YouTube titled “I Am Sarah” and you should definitely see it. The movie, written and Produced by Peace Adewale, is dedicated to Leah Sharibu, a teenager who was kidnapped along with her schoolmates from the Government Girls Science and Technical Secondary School, Dapchi, Yobe in 2018. While the other girls were returned, Leah was held by her captors who insisted she change her religion. “I Am Sarah” was directed by Wole Soyinka. Watch the short film below:   The best Nigerian and African video content from around the web specially curated for YOU! 